rComments: Dr. Quinlan was the best prof I've had so far (in my meager first year). Her lectures are well-detailed, and she takes time to demonstrate how to apply the concepts learned in the slides. This doesn't mean the course is easy - you still have to do your HW if you want to succeed, but Quinlan definitely makes it easier. Bless her and her kind soul.

It wasn't great being a first-year student at a gigantic school like U of T, and having one of my first experiences in class be with Quinlan. The shrillness of her voice kept me on edge the entire time for the wrong reasons, and she went through material so incredibly fast, that if you blink you'll be finished with an entire topic. Glad it's over.
